;The origins of Lightbeam
Datblygu Lightbeam


;Lightbeam began in July 2011 as Collusion, a personal project by Mozilla software developer <a href="%s">Atul Varma</a>.
Cychwynnwyd Lightbeam yng Ngorffennaf 2011 fel Collusion, project personol project gan ddatblygwr meddalwedd ym Mozilla, <a href="%s">Atul Varma</a>.


;Inspired by the book, <em>The Filter Bubble</em>, Atul created an experimental add-on to visualize browsing behavior and data collection on the Web.
Wedi ei ysbrydoli gan y llyfr, <em>The Filter Bubble</em>, creodd Atul ychwanegyn arbrofol er mwyn dangos arferion pori a chasglu data ar y we.


;In February 2012, Gary Kovacs, Mozilla CEO at the time, introduced the Collusion add-on in a <a href="%s">TED talk</a> (now one of the most watched TED talks of all time) about exposing online tracking.
Ym mis Chwefror 2012, cyflwynodd Gary Kovacs, Prif Swyddog Gweithredol Mozilla ar y pryd, yr ychwanegyn Collusion mewn <a href="%s">cyflwyniad TED</a> (erbyn hyn yn un o'r cyflwyniadau TED sydd wedi eu gwylio amlaf) er mwyn amlygu tracio ar-lein.


;In September 2012, Mozilla joined forces with faculty and student researchers at <a href="%s">Emily Carr University of Art + Design</a> to develop and implement visualizations for the add-on.
Ym mis Medi 2012, ymunodd Mozilla gyda myfyrwyr yn yr <a href="%s">Emily Carr University of Art + Design</a> i ddatblygu a gwireddu dull o amlygu'r data ar gyfer yr ychwanegyn.


;With the support of the Ford Foundation and the Natural Sciences and Engineering Research Council (NSERC), Collusion has been re-imagined as Lightbeam and was launched in the fall of 2013.
Gyda chefnogaeth y Ford Foundation a'r Natural Sciences and Engineering Research Council (NSERC), mae Collusion wedi ei ail greu fel Lightbeam a'i lansio yn yr hydref yn 2013.


